Carlo Ratti: Real Time City

URL = http://world-information.org/wio/program/paris/1245864194/htmlPublicWIOPlayer?mid=wio/carlo_ratti_lecture.flv

=Description=

	
"The real-time city is now real! The increasing deployment of sensors and hand-held electronics in recent years is allowing a new approach to the study of the built environment. The way we describe and understand cities is being radically transformed - alongside the tools we use to design them and impact on their physical structure. Studying these changes from a critical point of view and anticipating them is the goal of the SENSEable City Laboratory, a multidisciplinary research initiative at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology."
(http://world-information.org/wio/program/paris/1245864194)


